{"id":1005289853,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"4 months, 1 week","timestamp":1690459029,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"27 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1005289853/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Contiguous Array","memory":"54 MB","code":"class Solution {\n    public int findMaxLength(int[] nums) {\n        \n        int n = nums.length;\n        Map<Integer, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();\n        int[] freq = new int[2];\n\n        map.put(0, -1);\n        int max = 0;\n\n        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {\n            freq[nums[i]]++;\n            int key = freq[1] - freq[0];\n            if(map.containsKey(key)) {\n                max = Math.max(max, i - map.get(key));\n            } else map.put(key, i);\n        }\n\n        return max;\n    } \n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"contiguous-array","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
